{"add":{"doc":{"id":"f4b22047be01bf23e007dab2bd104fe37c18fbb2fa77c41a373ab551a2d80541","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/41/Tribal_Linguistic_map_Zambia.jpg/350px-Tribal_Linguistic_map_Zambia.jpg","previous":[],"after":["The population comprises approximately 73 ethnic groups, most of which are Bantu-speaking. Almost 90% of Zambians belong to the nine main ethnolinguistic groups: the Nyanja-Chewa, Bemba, Tonga, Tumbuka, Lunda, Luvale, Kaonde, Nkoya and Lozi. In the rural areas, each ethnic group is concentrated in a particular geographic region of the country and many groups are very small and not as well known. However, all the ethnic groups can be found in significant numbers in Lusaka and the Copperbelt."]}}}